Steve...Quoted from the MERCK VETERINARY MANUAL re: rabies: "hematogenous
spread can occur, but is rare".
I guess a person can make of that whatever they want to vis a vis spread via
body fluids. As a matter of fact, now that I'm thinking of it, there is a
case on record where a person contracted rabies when he received a corneal
transplant from a donor who died of the disease (misdiagnosed as a stroke)!!
